    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm going to close this issue as the wiki mentioned above now documents using the Postman file (and I will update that page with new information).\r\n\r\nIn the PR I will post later this morning, I've used the PostMan file to do three things:\r\n\r\n1. Testing the RPC routines (obviously). There is currently one test request for each RPC routing, testing expected behavior. In the future, I'd like to extend this to include unexpected behavior such as invalid input.\r\n2. I used the documentation at the head of each Postman request to generate automated documentation in the `./docs/readthedocs/source/rpc/index.rst` file. Eventually this can be automated to be built during CI.\r\n3. I used the same documentation to make the comments in the source code for each RPC routine. I also double checked that each routine's interface agrees with each routines documentation. (They mostly do...)\r\n\r\nClosing....",
